{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843706223,"sessionID":"ses_28777d91dffenRpzIsVZJrnayP","part":{"id":"prt_d78887df1001Y0VcedlbGumSHn","messageID":"msg_d78886fbb0012xV2PqJcOO1NX3","sessionID":"ses_28777d91dffenRpzIsVZJrnayP","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_7a35b115e05848f5b5551862","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Sandbox creation handler in `pkg/workloadmanager`. The Sandbox creation handler is responsible for provisioning sandboxed execution environments based on AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter configurations.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-005\n10: - **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n11: - **Language**: Go\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: - **Depends On**: AR-004 (WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架), client-go library\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Scenario: Sandbox Resource Creation\n18: \n19: ### AR-005-001: Create Sandbox from AgentRuntime\n20: \n21: - **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime resource in namespace \"default\" with valid TargetPorts and PodTemplate\n22: - **WHEN** a POST request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/{name}/sandbox` to create a new sandbox\n23: - **THEN** the handler SHALL parse the AgentRuntime specification\n24: - **AND** SHALL create a Pod matching the PodTemplate specification\n25: - **AND** SHALL set appropriate labels to link the sandbox to the parent AgentRuntime\n26: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 201 Created with sandbox identification information\n27: \n28: ### AR-005-002: Create Sandbox from CodeInterpreter\n29: \n30: - **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter resource in namespace \"default\" with valid Template configuration\n31: - **WHEN** a POST request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/codeinterpreters/{name}/sandbox` to create a new sandbox\n32: - **THEN** the handler SHALL parse the CodeInterpreter template specification\n33: - **AND** SHALL create a Pod using the ContainerTemplateSpec\n34: - **AND** SHALL apply warm pool logic if WarmPoolSize > 0\n35: - **AND** SHALL set appropriate labels to link the sandbox to the parent CodeInterpreter\n36: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 201 Created with sandbox identification information\n37: \n38: ### AR-005-003: Sandbox creation with custom parameters\n39: \n40: - **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter resource\n41: - **WHEN** a POST request includes custom override parameters in the request body\n42: - **THEN** the handler SHALL apply the overrides to the sandbox specification\n43: - **AND** SHALL validate that override values meet validation constraints\n44: - **AND** SHALL merge overrides with the base template\n45: \n46: ### AR-005-004: Sandbox creation validation failure\n47: \n48: - **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime with invalid PodTemplate (e.g., missing required container image)\n49: - **WHEN** a POST request attempts to create a sandbox\n50: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return HTTP 400 Bad Request\n51: - **AND** SHALL include validation error details in the response\n52: \n53: ### AR-005-005: Sandbox creation for non-existent resource\n54: \n55: - **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n56: - **WHEN** a POST request targets a non-existent AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter\n57: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ## Scenario: Sandbox Lifecycle Management\n62: \n63: ### AR-005-010: Get Sandbox Status\n64: \n65: - **GIVEN** a running HTTP server with active sandboxes\n66: - **WHEN** a GET request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/{name}`\n67: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return the current sandbox status including:\n68:   - Pod phase (Pending, Running, Succeeded, Failed, Unknown)\n69:   - Container states\n70:   - IP address if assigned\n71:   - Creation timestamp\n72:   - Parent resource reference (AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter)\n73: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK\n74: \n75: ### AR-005-011: List Sandboxes\n76: \n77: - **GIVEN** multiple sandbox instances running in a namespace\n78: - **WHEN** a GET request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes`\n79: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return a list of all sandboxes in the namespace\n80: - **AND** SHALL support labelSelector query parameter for filtering\n81: - **AND** SHALL include sandbox metadata and status summary\n82: \n83: ### AR-005-012: Delete Sandbox\n84: \n85: - **GIVEN** an existing sandbox instance\n86: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/{name}`\n87: - **THEN** the handler SHALL terminate the sandbox Pod\n88: - **AND** SHALL clean up associated resources (services, configmaps)\n89: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with deletion confirmation\n90: \n91: ### AR-005-013: Delete Sandbox with force option\n92: \n93: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with terminating Pod that fails to stop gracefully\n94: - **WHEN** a DELETE request includes `gracePeriodSeconds=0` and `force=true`\n95: - **THEN** the handler SHALL forcefully terminate the sandbox\n96: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK\n97: \n98: ### AR-005-014: Watch Sandboxes\n99: \n100: - **GIVEN** multiple sandbox instances\n101: - **WHEN** a GET request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes?watch=true`\n102: - **THEN** the server SHALL stream sandbox events as NDJSON\n103: - **AND** SHALL send ADDED, MODIFIED, and DELETED events as sandboxes change state\n104: \n105: ---\n106: \n107: ## Scenario: Sandbox Template Processing\n108: \n109: ### AR-005-020: Process AgentRuntime PodTemplate\n110: \n111: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with a PodTemplate containing custom containers, volumes, and node selectors\n112: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox from this AgentRuntime\n113: - **THEN** the handler SHALL merge the PodTemplate.Spec with default values\n114: - **AND** SHALL apply the specified NodeSelector, Affinity, and Tolerations\n115: - **AND** SHALL preserve InitContainers if specified\n116: \n117: ### AR-005-021: Process CodeInterpreter ContainerTemplate\n118: \n119: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with a ContainerTemplate (image, command, args, env, resources)\n120: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox from this CodeInterpreter\n121: - **THEN** the handler SHALL create a Pod with a single container from the template\n122: - **AND** SHALL apply resource requirements from the template\n123: - **AND** SHALL set the RuntimeClassName if specified\n124: \n125: ### AR-005-022: Apply Security Context\n126: \n127: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter with SecurityContext configured\n128: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n129: - **THEN** the handler SHALL apply PodSecurityContext to the Pod\n130: - **AND** SHALL apply SecurityContext to each container\n131: - **AND** SHALL validate security context values against policy\n132: \n133: ### AR-005-023: Inject Environment Variables\n134: \n135: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter with Env variables in the template\n136: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n137: - **THEN** the handler SHALL inject the specified environment variables\n138: - **AND** SHALL support both static values and references (e.g., from secrets, configmaps)\n139: \n140: ---\n141: \n142: ## Scenario: Sandbox Pool Management\n143: \n144: ### AR-005-030: Warm Pool Pre-provisioning\n145: \n146: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with WarmPoolSize = 3\n147: - **WHEN** the CodeInterpreter is created or becomes ready\n148: - **THEN** the handler SHALL proactively create 3 sandbox Pods\n149: - **AND** SHALL mark them as warm/ready\n150: - **AND** SHALL maintain the warm pool size\n151: \n152: ### AR-005-031: Warm Pool Scaling\n153: \n154: - **GIVEN** a warm pool with 3 ready sandboxes\n155: - **WHEN** a new sandbox request arrives and all warm sandboxes are in use\n156: - **THEN** the handler SHALL create an additional sandbox to handle the request\n157: - **AND** SHALL attempt to maintain the warm pool size\n158: \n159: ### AR-005-032: Warm Pool Cleanup\n160: \n161: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with WarmPoolSize reduced from 5 to 2\n162: - **WHEN** the pool size change is detected\n163: - **THEN** the handler SHALL terminate excess warm sandboxes\n164: - **AND** SHALL gracefully drain unused sandboxes first\n165: \n166: ---\n167: \n168: ## Scenario: Sandbox Networking\n169: \n170: ### AR-005-040: Expose Sandbox Ports\n171: \n172: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with TargetPorts configured (port 8080, protocol HTTP)\n173: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n174: - **THEN** the handler SHALL create a Service exposing the specified ports\n175: - **AND** SHALL set up appropriate network policies if configured\n176: - **AND** SHALL configure ingress routing based on PathPrefix\n177: \n178: ### AR-005-041: Sandbox Ingress Configuration\n179: \n180: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with TargetPorts including PathPrefix \"/api\"\n181: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n182: - **THEN** the handler SHALL configure ingress rules for the specified path\n183: - **AND** SHALL ensure the path prefix is routed to the correct container port\n184: \n185: ### AR-005-042: Network Policy Enforcement\n186: \n187: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with network policy requirements\n188: - **WHEN** creating network resources\n189: - **THEN** the handler SHALL apply NetworkPolicy resources to restrict traffic\n190: - **AND** SHALL support both ingress and egress rules\n191: \n192: ---\n193: \n194: ## Scenario: Sandbox Scheduling\n195: \n196: ### AR-005-050: Node Selection\n197: \n198: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with NodeSelector configured (disktype=ssd, region=us-west)\n199: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n200: - **THEN** the handler SHALL schedule the Pod on a node matching the node selectors\n201: - **AND** SHALL handle scheduling failures gracefully\n202: \n203: ### AR-005-051: Affinity and Anti-Affinity\n204: \n205: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with Affinity rules (podAntiAffinity, nodeAffinity)\n206: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n207: - **THEN** the handler SHALL apply the affinity rules to Pod scheduling\n208: - **AND** SHALL respect both required and preferred affinity rules\n209: \n210: ### AR-005-052: Resource Quota Enforcement\n211: \n212: - **GIVEN** a namespace with ResourceQuota limiting CPU, memory, or pod count\n213: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox exceeds quota\n214: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return HTTP 403 Forbidden\n215: - **AND** SHALL include quota violation details in the response\n216: \n217: ---\n218: \n219: ## Scenario: Error Handling and Recovery\n220: \n221: ### AR-005-060: Pod Creation Failure\n222: \n223: - **GIVEN** a sandbox creation request\n224: - **WHEN** the Kubernetes API returns an error during Pod creation\n225: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return appropriate HTTP status code (4xx or 5xx)\n226: - **AND** SHALL include error message with cause details\n227: - **AND** SHALL log the error for debugging\n228: \n229: ### AR-005-061: Sandbox Status Sync\n230: \n231: - **GIVEN** a sandbox whose Pod has crashed or been killed externally\n232: - **WHEN** querying sandbox status\n233: - **THEN** the handler SHALL detect the stale state\n234: - **AND** SHALL update the sandbox status to reflect the actual Pod state\n235: - **AND** SHALL emit events for status changes\n236: \n237: ### AR-005-062: Graceful Shutdown\n238: \n239: - **GIVEN** a running sandbox\n240: - **WHEN** the WorkloadManager receives shutdown signal\n241: - **THEN** the handler SHALL not accept new sandbox requests\n242: - **AND** SHALL wait for in-flight sandbox creations to complete\n243: - **AND** SHALL not terminate existing sandboxes (responsibility of controller)\n244: \n245: ---\n246: \n247: ## References\n248: \n249: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md`\n250: - Related AR: AR-004 (WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架)\n251: - AgentRuntime CRD: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n252: - CodeInterpreter CRD: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n253: - client-go library: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`\n254: - API group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n\n(End of file - total 254 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Sandbox creation handler in `pkg/workloadmanager`. The Sandbox creation handler is responsible for provisioning sandboxed execution environments based on AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter configurations.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-005\n- **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n- **Depends On**: AR-004 (WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架), client-go library\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Sandbox Resource Creation\n\n### AR-005-001: Create Sandbox from AgentRuntime\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775843706208,"end":1775843706221}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843706236,"sessionID":"ses_28777d91dffenRpzIsVZJrnayP","part":{"id":"prt_d788881d4001Zqpe9Yv424R80Z","messageID":"msg_d78886fbb0012xV2PqJcOO1NX3","sessionID":"ses_28777d91dffenRpzIsVZJrnayP","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_aa1df64ccf284a9ca6eda77b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package v1alpha1\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n5: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n6: )\n7: \n8: // +genclient\n9: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n10: // +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n11: // +kubebuilder:resource:shortName=ar\n12: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\n13: \n14: // AgentRuntime defines runtime configuration for agent sessions.\n15: type AgentRuntime struct {\n16: \tmetav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n17: \tmetav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n18: \n19: \tSpec   AgentRuntimeSpec   `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n20: \tStatus AgentRuntimeStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n21: }\n22: \n23: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n24: \n25: // AgentRuntimeList contains a list of AgentRuntime.\n26: type AgentRuntimeList struct {\n27: \tmetav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n28: \tmetav1.ListMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n29: \tItems           []AgentRuntime `json:\"items\"`\n30: }\n31: \n32: // AgentRuntimeSpec defines the desired state of AgentRuntime.\n33: type AgentRuntimeSpec struct {\n34: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n35: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Pattern:=`^(\\d+h)(\\d+m)?$`\n36: \t// +kubebuilder:default:=\"8h\"\n37: \tMaxSessionDuration string `json:\"maxSessionDuration\"`\n38: \n39: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n40: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Pattern:=`^(\\d+m)|(\\d+h)(\\d+m)?$`\n41: \t// +kubebuilder:default:=\"15m\"\n42: \tSessionTimeout string `json:\"sessionTimeout\"`\n43: \n44: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n45: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:MinItems:=1\n46: \tTargetPorts []TargetPort `json:\"targetPorts\"`\n47: \n48: \t// +optional\n49: \tPodTemplate *PodTemplateSpec `json:\"podTemplate,omitempty\"`\n50: }\n51: \n52: // AgentRuntimeStatus defines the observed state of AgentRuntime.\n53: type AgentRuntimeStatus struct {\n54: \t// +optional\n55: \tConditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n56: \n57: \t// +optional\n58: \tObservedGeneration int64 `json:\"observedGeneration,omitempty\"`\n59: }\n60: \n61: // +genclient\n62: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n63: // +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n64: // +kubebuilder:resource:shortName=ci\n65: \n66: // CodeInterpreter defines code execution environment specifications.\n67: type CodeInterpreter struct {\n68: \tmetav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n69: \tmetav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n70: \n71: \tSpec   CodeInterpreterSpec   `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n72: \tStatus CodeInterpreterStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n73: }\n74: \n75: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n76: \n77: // CodeInterpreterList contains a list of CodeInterpreter.\n78: type CodeInterpreterList struct {\n79: \tmetav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n80: \tmetav1.ListMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n81: \tItems           []CodeInterpreter `json:\"items\"`\n82: }\n83: \n84: // CodeInterpreterSpec defines the desired state of CodeInterpreter.\n85: type CodeInterpreterSpec struct {\n86: \t// +optional\n87: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=picod;none\n88: \t// +kubebuilder:default:=picod\n89: \tAuthMode AuthMode `json:\"authMode,omitempty\"`\n90: \n91: \t// +optional\n92: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Pattern:=`^(\\d+h)(\\d+m)?$`\n93: \t// +kubebuilder:default:=\"8h\"\n94: \tMaxSessionDuration string `json:\"maxSessionDuration,omitempty\"`\n95: \n96: \t// +optional\n97: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Pattern:=`^(\\d+m)|(\\d+h)(\\d+m)?$`\n98: \t// +kubebuilder:default:=\"15m\"\n99: \tSessionTimeout string `json:\"sessionTimeout,omitempty\"`\n100: \n101: \t// +optional\n102: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:MinItems:=0\n103: \tPorts []TargetPort `json:\"ports,omitempty\"`\n104: \n105: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n106: \tTemplate ContainerTemplateSpec `json:\"template\"`\n107: \n108: \t// +optional\n109: \t// +kubebuilder:default:=0\n110: \tWarmPoolSize int32 `json:\"warmPoolSize,omitempty\"`\n111: }\n112: \n113: // CodeInterpreterStatus defines the observed state of CodeInterpreter.\n114: type CodeInterpreterStatus struct {\n115: \t// +optional\n116: \tConditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n117: \n118: \t// +optional\n119: \tObservedGeneration int64 `json:\"observedGeneration,omitempty\"`\n120: \n121: \t// +optional\n122: \tReady bool `json:\"ready\"`\n123: }\n124: \n125: // TargetPort defines port configuration for the runtime.\n126: type TargetPort struct {\n127: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n128: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum:=1\n129: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Maximum:=65535\n130: \tPort int32 `json:\"port\"`\n131: \n132: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n133: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=HTTP;HTTPS\n134: \tProtocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n135: \n136: \t// +optional\n137: \tName string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n138: \n139: \t// +optional\n140: \tPathPrefix string `json:\"pathPrefix,omitempty\"`\n141: }\n142: \n143: // PodTemplateSpec defines a custom pod template for the runtime.\n144: type PodTemplateSpec struct {\n145: \tmetav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n146: \tSpec              *PodSpec `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n147: }\n148: \n149: // PodSpec is a selective subset of corev1.PodSpec.\n150: type PodSpec struct {\n151: \t// +optional\n152: \tContainers []ContainerSpec `json:\"containers,omitempty\"`\n153: \n154: \t// +optional\n155: \tVolumes []corev1.Volume `json:\" volumes,omitempty\"`\n156: \n157: \t// +optional\n158: \tRestartPolicy corev1.RestartPolicy `json:\"restartPolicy,omitempty\"`\n159: \n160: \t// +optional\n161: \tServiceAccountName string `json:\"serviceAccountName,omitempty\"`\n162: \n163: \t// +optional\n164: \tNodeSelector map[string]string `json:\"nodeSelector,omitempty\"`\n165: \n166: \t// +optional\n167: \tAffinity *corev1.Affinity `json:\"affinity,omitempty\"`\n168: \n169: \t// +optional\n170: \tTolerations []corev1.Toleration `json:\"tolerations,omitempty\"`\n171: \n172: \t// +optional\n173: \tPriorityClassName string `json:\"priorityClassName,omitempty\"`\n174: \n175: \t// +optional\n176: \tPriority *int32 `json:\"priority,omitempty\"`\n177: \n178: \t// +optional\n179: \tDNSPolicy corev1.DNSPolicy `json:\"dnsPolicy,omitempty\"`\n180: \n181: \t// +optional\n182: \tHostNetwork bool `json:\"hostNetwork,omitempty\"`\n183: \n184: \t// +optional\n185: \tHostPID bool `json:\"hostPID,omitempty\"`\n186: \n187: \t// +optional\n188: \tHostIPC bool `json:\"hostIPC,omitempty\"`\n189: \n190: \t// +optional\n191: \tSecurityContext *corev1.PodSecurityContext `json:\"securityContext,omitempty\"`\n192: \n193: \t// +optional\n194: \tImagePullSecrets []corev1.LocalObjectReference `json:\"imagePullSecrets,omitempty\"`\n195: \n196: \t// +optional\n197: \tInitContainers []ContainerSpec `json:\"initContainers,omitempty\"`\n198: }\n199: \n200: // ContainerSpec is a selective subset of corev1.Container.\n201: type ContainerSpec struct {\n202: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n203: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n204: \n205: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n206: \tImage string `json:\"image\"`\n207: \n208: \t// +optional\n209: \tCommand []string `json:\"command,omitempty\"`\n210: \n211: \t// +optional\n212: \tArgs []string `json:\"args,omitempty\"`\n213: \n214: \t// +optional\n215: \tEnv []corev1.EnvVar `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n216: \n217: \t// +optional\n218: \tResources corev1.ResourceRequirements `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n219: \n220: \t// +optional\n221: \tImagePullPolicy corev1.PullPolicy `json:\"imagePullPolicy,omitempty\"`\n222: \n223: \t// +optional\n224: \tPorts []corev1.ContainerPort `json:\"ports,omitempty\"`\n225: \n226: \t// +optional\n227: \tLivenessProbe *corev1.Probe `json:\"livenessProbe,omitempty\"`\n228: \n229: \t// +optional\n230: \tReadinessProbe *corev1.Probe `json:\"readinessProbe,omitempty\"`\n231: \n232: \t// +optional\n233: \tStartupProbe *corev1.Probe `json:\"startupProbe,omitempty\"`\n234: \n235: \t// +optional\n236: \tVolumeMounts []corev1.VolumeMount `json:\"volumeMounts,omitempty\"`\n237: \n238: \t// +optional\n239: \tSecurityContext *corev1.SecurityContext `json:\"securityContext,omitempty\"`\n240: }\n241: \n242: // ContainerTemplateSpec defines container specification for CodeInterpreter.\n243: type ContainerTemplateSpec struct {\n244: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n245: \tImage string `json:\"image\"`\n246: \n247: \t// +optional\n248: \tCommand []string `json:\"command,omitempty\"`\n249: \n250: \t// +optional\n251: \tArgs []string `json:\"args,omitempty\"`\n252: \n253: \t// +optional\n254: \tEnv []corev1.EnvVar `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n255: \n256: \t// +optional\n257: \tResources corev1.ResourceRequirements `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n258: \n259: \t// +optional\n260: \tRuntimeClassName *string `json:\"runtimeClassName,omitempty\"`\n261: }\n262: \n263: // AuthMode defines the authentication mode for CodeInterpreter.\n264: type AuthMode string\n265: \n266: const (\n267: \t// AuthModePicod uses picod authentication.\n268: \tAuthModePicod AuthMode = \"picod\"\n269: \n270: \t// AuthModeNone means no authentication.\n271: \tAuthModeNone AuthMode = \"none\"\n272: )\n\n(End of file - total 272 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package v1alpha1\n\nimport (\n\tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n\tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n)\n\n// +genclient\n// +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n// +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n// +kubebuilder:resource:shortName=ar\n// +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\n\n// AgentRuntime defines runtime configuration for agent sessions.\ntype AgentRuntime struct {\n\tmetav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n\tmetav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n\n\tSpec   AgentRuntimeSpec   `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n\tStatus AgentRuntimeStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go","time":{"start":1775843706211,"end":1775843706234}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775843706276,"sessionID":"ses_28777d91dffenRpzIsVZJrnayP","part":{"id":"prt_d7888857c001jwR4pM5qT5Zj3Z","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d78886fbb0012xV2PqJcOO1NX3","sessionID":"ses_28777d91dffenRpzIsVZJrnayP","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":23719,"input":1139,"output":191,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":22389}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775843711442,"sessionID":"ses_28777d91dffenRpzIsVZJrnayP","part":{"id":"prt_d788899d0001J1M8VNxaUCux6S","messageID":"msg_d788885d0001Dz3E7ZAQKpiVeg","sessionID":"ses_28777d91dffenRpzIsVZJrnayP","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843713835,"sessionID":"ses_28777d91dffenRpzIsVZJrnayP","part":{"id":"prt_d78889e82001zRgiTMCLRE7PNa","messageID":"msg_d788885d0001Dz3E7ZAQKpiVeg","sessionID":"ses_28777d91dffenRpzIsVZJrnayP","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_80767d426cb94ff79f3440db","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/sandbox-orchestration/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/sandbox-orchestration/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Sandbox Orchestration Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Orchestrate agent sandboxes via Kubernetes CRDs (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter), a Gin HTTP API (workload manager), session persistence, garbage collection, and optional service-account authentication.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime CRD schema and API registration\n9: The system SHALL expose a namespaced `AgentRuntime` custom resource in API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, with subresource `status`, print column `Age` from `.metadata.creationTimestamp`, and SHALL register list kind `AgentRuntimeList`.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Group version and resource naming\n12: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API client resolving the CRD\n13: - **WHEN** the group, version, and kind are read from type metadata\n14: - **THEN** `GroupVersion` is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`, kind `AgentRuntime`, and GVR resource name is `agentruntimes`\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime spec fields and kubebuilder rules\n17: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeSpec` with: `Ports` as `[]TargetPort` serialized under JSON key `targetPort`; required `Template` (`*SandboxTemplate`) under JSON key `podTemplate`; required `SessionTimeout` (`*metav1.Duration`) under `sessionTimeout` with kubebuilder default `\"15m\"`; required `MaxSessionDuration` (`*metav1.Duration`) under `maxSessionDuration` with kubebuilder default `\"8h\"`.\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: SandboxTemplate embeds Pod spec\n20: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` with `spec.podTemplate`\n21: - **WHEN** the template is deserialized\n22: - **THEN** `labels` and `annotations` are optional maps and `spec` is required and of type `corev1.PodSpec`\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime status\n25: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeStatus` with optional `conditions` of type `[]metav1.Condition`.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Conditions optional\n28: - **GIVEN** a minimal `AgentRuntime` object\n29: - **WHEN** status is omitted or empty\n30: - **THEN** deserialization succeeds without requiring `conditions`\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter CRD schema\n33: The system SHALL expose a namespaced `CodeInterpreter` CRD in the same API group/version with subresource `status` and print column `Age` from `.metadata.creationTimestamp`.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter GVR\n36: - **GIVEN** dynamic client configuration for workload templates\n37: - **WHEN** GVR is constructed for `codeinterpreters`\n38: - **THEN** group is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, resource `codeinterpreters`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterSpec fields\n41: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterSpec` with: optional `Ports` (`[]TargetPort`, JSON `ports`); required `Template` (`*CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`, JSON `template`); optional `SessionTimeout` with default `\"15m\"`; optional `MaxSessionDuration` with default `\"8h\"`; optional `WarmPoolSize` (`*int32`); optional `AuthMode` (`AuthModeType`, JSON `authMode`) with default `\"picod\"` and enum `picod` or `none`.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Auth mode constants\n44: - **GIVEN** API constants for auth mode\n45: - **WHEN** `AuthMode` is compared\n46: - **THEN** `AuthModePicoD` equals `\"picod\"` and `AuthModeNone` equals `\"none\"`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterStatus fields\n49: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterStatus` with optional `conditions` and optional boolean `ready`.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Ready flag\n52: - **GIVEN** a reconciled `CodeInterpreter`\n53: - **WHEN** status is updated by the controller\n54: - **THEN** `status.ready` may be set to `true` alongside a `Ready` condition\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: TargetPort and Protocol types\n57: The system SHALL define `TargetPort` with optional `pathPrefix`, optional `name`, required `port` (`uint32`), and required `protocol` (`ProtocolType`) with kubebuilder default `HTTP` and enum `HTTP` or `HTTPS`.\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Protocol constants\n60: - **GIVEN** port configuration without explicit protocol in some code paths\n61: - **WHEN** defaults apply at API level\n62: - **THEN** default protocol is `HTTP` per kubebuilder marker\n63: \n64: ### Requirement: Workload manager health endpoint\n65: The system SHALL serve `GET /health` without authentication and SHALL respond `200` with JSON body `{\"status\":\"healthy\"}`.\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Health bypasses auth middleware\n68: - **GIVEN** `EnableAuth` is true\n69: - **WHEN** a client calls `GET /health` with no `Authorization` header\n70: - **THEN** the response status is 200 and body contains `\"status\":\"healthy\"`\n71: \n72: ### Requirement: Workload manager v1 routes and middleware\n73: The system SHALL mount a `/v1` route group with `loggingMiddleware` then `authMiddleware` (order preserved), and SHALL register `POST /v1/agent-runtime`, `DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId`, `POST /v1/code-interpreter`, and `DELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId`.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Session id path parameter\n76: - **GIVEN** a delete request\n77: - **WHEN** Gin binds the path\n78: - **THEN** the session identifier is read from parameter name `sessionId` (camelCase)\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: Create sandbox request validation\n81: The system SHALL accept JSON for create endpoints matching `CreateSandboxRequest` with fields `kind`, `name`, `namespace`; SHALL overwrite `kind` from the handler (`AgentRuntime` or `CodeInterpreter`); and SHALL reject requests where `kind` is not one of those, `namespace` is empty, or `name` is empty.\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Validation failure returns 400\n84: - **GIVEN** the handler sets `sandboxReq.Kind` from the route and `Validate()` is called\n85: - **WHEN** `namespace` or `name` is empty in the JSON body\n86: - **THEN** the response is 400 and the error message includes `required` (e.g. `namespace is required` or `name is required`)\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Create sandbox success response\n89: On successful creation the system SHALL respond `200` with `CreateSandboxResponse` containing `sessionId`, `sandboxId`, `sandboxName`, and `entryPoints` (each entry point has `path`, `protocol`, `endpoint`).\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Entry points reflect TargetPort and pod IP\n92: - **GIVEN** a sandbox reaches running state and pod IP is resolved\n93: - **WHEN** the response is built\n94: - **THEN** each entry point `endpoint` is `host:port` joined from pod IP and configured port, with protocol string from `TargetPort.Protocol`\n95: \n96: ### Requirement: Create sandbox error responses\n97: The system SHALL return `400` with `{\"message\":...}` for invalid JSON or validation failure; `404` with message from wrapped not-found errors when AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter is missing from informer cache; `401` with message from client extraction error when `EnableAuth` is true; `500` with `{\"message\":\"internal server error\"}` for other create failures including timeout.\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: JSON parse failure\n100: - **GIVEN** a non-JSON body to `POST /v1/agent-runtime`\n101: - **WHEN** the handler binds JSON\n102: - **THEN** status is 400 and message is `Invalid request body`\n103: \n104: ### Requirement: Optional Bearer authentication via TokenReview\n105: When `EnableAuth` is true, the system SHALL require header `Authorization: Bearer <token>` with exactly two space-separated fields; SHALL validate via `authentication/v1` `TokenReview` create; SHALL cache results in an LRU cache (capacity 1000, entry TTL 5 minutes); and SHALL store in context: token, full username, service account name, namespace parsed from `system:serviceaccount:<ns>:<name>`.\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Missing header\n108: - **GIVEN** `EnableAuth` is true\n109: - **WHEN** `/v1/...` is called without `Authorization`\n110: - **THEN** response is 401 with message `Missing authorization header` and handler chain aborts\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: TokenReview success path\n113: - **GIVEN** a valid service account token and `EnableAuth` true\n114: - **WHEN** `validateServiceAccountToken` runs with cache miss\n115: - **THEN** the server creates `TokenReview` with `spec.token` set and uses `status.user.username` when `status.authenticated` is true\n116: \n117: ### Requirement: Authenticated Kubernetes operations use user client\n118: When `EnableAuth` is true, the system SHALL use a per-user dynamic client (from bearer token) for creating/deleting `Sandbox` or `SandboxClaim` resources; when false, SHALL use the manager’s in-cluster/default dynamic client.\n119: \n120: #### Scenario: User client cache key\n121: - **GIVEN** repeated requests from the same namespace and service account name\n122: - **WHEN** `GetOrCreateUserK8sClient` is used\n123: - **THEN** the cache key is `<namespace>:<serviceAccountName>`\n124: \n125: ### Requirement: Sandbox creation ordering and store placeholder\n126: The system SHALL call `StoreSandbox` with a placeholder `SandboxInfo` before creating the `Sandbox` or `SandboxClaim` in the API; SHALL register a one-shot watcher before create; SHALL wait up to 2 minutes for sandbox status `running` from the reconciler; SHALL resolve pod IP and then `UpdateSandbox` with full info; and SHALL roll back the created CR on failure after the wait (delete Sandbox or SandboxClaim within a 30s timeout context).\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Watcher registration before create\n129: - **GIVEN** a create request reaches `createSandbox`\n130: - **WHEN** the Sandbox CR is created\n131: - **THEN** `WatchSandboxOnce` was already invoked for that namespace/name\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Timeout returns error\n134: - **GIVEN** no running notification within 2 minutes\n135: - **WHEN** the select completes\n136: - **THEN** creation fails with error `sandbox creation timed out` and HTTP 500 is returned to the client\n137: \n138: ### Requirement: Pod IP resolution\n139: The system SHALL prefer pod name equal to sandbox name; if annotation `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name` exists on the created Sandbox (from agent-sandbox controller), SHALL use that as pod name; SHALL load pod from informer cache and require `PodRunning` and non-empty `PodIP`; otherwise SHALL list pods by label `runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name=<sandboxName>` and pick the pod whose controller owner reference is kind `Sandbox` and name matches.\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: Pod not running yields error\n142: - **GIVEN** a matching pod in non-Running phase\n143: - **WHEN** IP is resolved\n144: - **THEN** resolution fails with an error indicating the pod is not running\n145: \n146: ### Requirement: Delete sandbox by session\n147: The system SHALL load session from store by `sessionId`; on `ErrNotFound` return `404` with message `Session ID <id> not found, maybe already deleted`; delete `SandboxClaim` when stored `Kind` is `SandboxClaim`, else delete `Sandbox`; treat API `NotFound` on delete as success; then `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`; success response `200` `{\"message\":\"Sandbox deleted successfully\"}`.\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: Store miss\n150: - **GIVEN** no session key in store\n151: - **WHEN** DELETE is invoked\n152: - **THEN** HTTP status is 404 and message mentions the session id\n153: \n154: ### Requirement: Garbage collection loop\n155: The system SHALL run a background goroutine tick every 15 seconds; each tick SHALL use a context timeout of 2 minutes; SHALL query inactive sessions with cutoff `now - 15m` and batch limit 16; SHALL query expired sessions with `before = now` and batch limit 16; SHALL merge lists and delete each unique workload then remove store entry by session ID.\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: GC uses DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout\n158: - **GIVEN** GC lists inactive sandboxes\n159: - **WHEN** computing the inactive cutoff\n160: - **THEN** `inactiveTime` equals `time.Now().Add(-DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout)` where `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout` is 15 minutes\n161: \n162: ### Requirement: HTTP server and process behavior\n163: The system SHALL use Gin with `gin.New()` for the workload API; SHALL serve with `h2c` wrapping and `http2.Server`; SHALL use `ReadTimeout` 15s and `IdleTimeout` 90s for HTTP when not using TLS; SHALL ping the store before listening; SHALL sync informers (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, Pod) with up to 1 minute wait; on SIGINT/SIGTERM SHALL shutdown HTTP within 15s, cancel context, wait for background workers, then `Close()` the store.\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: TLS requires cert and key\n166: - **GIVEN** `EnableTLS` is true and cert or key path is empty\n167: - **WHEN** `Start` runs\n168: - **THEN** it returns an error that TLS is enabled but cert/key not provided\n169: \n170: ### Requirement: API error helper constants\n171: The system SHALL define in package `api` the sentinel errors `ErrAgentRuntimeNotFound`, `ErrCodeInterpreterNotFound`, `ErrTemplateMissing`, `ErrPublicKeyMissing`, and SHALL map `CodeInterpreter` kind to group-resource `agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters` and default kinds to `agentcube.volcano.sh/agentruntimes` for `NewSandboxTemplateNotFoundError`.\n172: \n173: #### Scenario: Session not found uses API machinery\n174: - **GIVEN** `NewSessionNotFoundError(\"sid\")`\n175: - **WHEN** the error is inspected as `APIStatus`\n176: - **THEN** the group resource is `agentcube.volcano.sh, Resource=sessions` and name is the session id\n\n(End of file - total 176 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Sandbox Orchestration Specification\n\n## Purpose\nOrchestrate agent sandboxes via Kubernetes CRDs (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter), a Gin HTTP API (workload manager), session persistence, garbage collection, and optional service-account authentication.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntime CRD schema and API registration\nThe system SHALL expose a namespaced `AgentRuntime` custom resource in API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, with subresource `status`, print column `Age` from `.metadata.creationTimestamp`, and SHALL register list kind `AgentRuntimeList`.\n\n#### Scenario: Group version and resource naming\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API client resolving the CRD\n- **WHEN** the group, version, and kind are read from type metadata\n- **THEN** `GroupVersion` is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`, kind `AgentRuntime`, and GVR resource name is `agentruntimes`\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntime spec fields and kubebuilder rules\nThe system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeSpec` with: `Ports` as `[]TargetPort` serialized under JSON key `targetPort`; required `Template` (`*SandboxTemplate`) under JSON key `podTemplate`; required `SessionTimeout` (`*metav1.Duration`) under `sessionTimeout` with kubebuilder default `\"15m\"`; required `MaxSessionDuration` (`*metav1.Duration`) under `maxSessionDuration` with kubebuilder default `\"8h\"`.\n\n#### Scenario: SandboxTemplate embeds Pod spec\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` with `spec.podTemplate`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/sandbox-orchestration/spec.md","time":{"start":1775843713810,"end":1775843713831}}}}
