{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843727772,"sessionID":"ses_28777d91dffenRpzIsVZJrnayP","part":{"id":"prt_d7888d579001EeEC3a83WBSiNW","messageID":"msg_d7888cc63001AV7eoGA0oqxeYW","sessionID":"ses_28777d91dffenRpzIsVZJrnayP","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_d74c451eb6374f39b10e58c4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Sandbox deletion and lifecycle management features in `pkg/workloadmanager`. This includes cleanup of expired sandboxes, graceful termination, force deletion, and lifecycle hooks.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-006\n10: - **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n11: - **Language**: Go\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: - **Depends On**: AR-005 (Sandbox 创建处理器)\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Scenario: Sandbox Deletion\n18: \n19: ### AR-006-001: Delete Sandbox by SessionID\n20: \n21: - **GIVEN** an existing sandbox with known SessionID\n22: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/{sessionId}`\n23: - **THEN** the handler SHALL locate the sandbox by SessionID\n24: - **AND** SHALL initiate Pod termination\n25: - **AND** SHALL clean up associated resources (services, configmaps)\n26: - **AND** SHALL remove the sandbox from the store\n27: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with deletion confirmation\n28: \n29: ### AR-006-002: Delete Sandbox by Name\n30: \n31: - **GIVEN** an existing sandbox with known name\n32: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/name/{name}`\n33: - **THEN** the handler SHALL locate the sandbox by name\n34: - **AND** SHALL perform the same cleanup as AR-006-001\n35: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK\n36: \n37: ### AR-006-003: Force Delete Sandbox\n38: \n39: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with terminating Pod that fails to stop gracefully (stuck in Terminating state > 5 minutes)\n40: - **WHEN** a DELETE request includes `gracePeriodSeconds=0` and `force=true`\n41: - **THEN** the handler SHALL forcefully delete the Pod using DeleteOptions\n42: - **AND** SHALL bypass finalizers if necessary\n43: - **AND** SHALL clean up all associated resources\n44: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK\n45: \n46: ### AR-006-004: Delete Non-existent Sandbox\n47: \n48: - **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n49: - **WHEN** a DELETE request targets a non-existent sandbox\n50: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n51: - **AND** SHALL include error message \"sandbox not found\"\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ## Scenario: Graceful Shutdown\n56: \n57: ### AR-006-010: Graceful Termination with Draining\n58: \n59: - **GIVEN** a running sandbox with active connections\n60: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is received with `gracePeriodSeconds=30`\n61: - **THEN** the handler SHALL send SIGTERM to the sandbox process\n62: - **AND** SHALL wait for grace period before force termination\n63: - **AND** SHALL allow in-flight requests to complete\n64: - **AND** SHALL reject new requests during grace period\n65: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK only after termination completes or grace period expires\n66: \n67: ### AR-006-011: Pre-delete Hook\n68: \n69: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with pre-delete lifecycle hook configured\n70: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is received\n71: - **THEN** the handler SHALL execute the pre-delete hook\n72: - **AND** SHALL wait for hook to complete (max 30 seconds)\n73: - **AND** SHALL proceed with deletion regardless of hook result\n74: - **AND** SHALL log hook execution status\n75: \n76: ### AR-006-012: Connection Draining\n77: \n78: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with active connections\n79: - **WHEN** graceful termination is initiated\n80: - **THEN** the handler SHALL stop routing new traffic to the sandbox\n81: - **AND** SHALL wait for existing connections to close (max grace period)\n82: - **AND** SHALL return \"draining\" status during the grace period\n83: \n84: ---\n85: \n86: ## Scenario: TTL and Expiration\n87: \n88: ### AR-006-020: Sandbox TTL Enforcement\n89: \n90: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with TTL set to 1 hour\n91: - **WHEN** the sandbox exceeds its TTL\n92: - **THEN** the garbage collector SHALL automatically delete the sandbox\n93: - **AND** SHALL emit an event for TTL expiration\n94: - **AND** SHALL clean up all associated resources\n95: - **AND** SHALL log the expiration for auditing\n96: \n97: ### AR-006-021: Idle Timeout\n98: \n99: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with IdleTimeout set to 10 minutes\n100: - **WHEN** no requests are received for 10 minutes\n101: - **THEN** the garbage collector SHALL mark the sandbox as idle\n102: - **AND** SHALL terminate idle sandboxes based on idle timeout policy\n103: - **AND** SHALL support both immediate deletion and graceful draining for idle sandboxes\n104: \n105: ### AR-006-022: Max Lifetime\n106: \n107: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with MaxLifetime set to 24 hours\n108: - **WHEN** the sandbox exceeds MaxLifetime\n109: - **THEN** the garbage collector SHALL reject new requests\n110: - **AND** SHALL terminate the sandbox after current requests complete\n111: - **AND** SHALL ensure sandboxes do not run indefinitely\n112: \n113: ---\n114: \n115: ## Scenario: Batch Operations\n116: \n117: ### AR-006-030: Delete All Sandboxes in Namespace\n118: \n119: - **GIVEN** multiple sandbox instances in a namespace\n120: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes` with `deleteAll=true`\n121: - **THEN** the handler SHALL delete all sandboxes in the namespace\n122: - **AND** SHALL return the count of deleted sandboxes\n123: - **AND** SHALL support async deletion for large batches\n124: \n125: ### AR-006-031: Delete Sandboxes by Label Selector\n126: \n127: - **GIVEN** multiple sandbox instances with various labels\n128: - **WHEN** a DELETE request includes `labelSelector=app=foo`\n129: - **THEN** the handler SHALL delete only sandboxes matching the label selector\n130: - **AND** SHALL return the count of deleted sandboxes\n131: \n132: ### AR-006-032: Delete Stale Sandboxes\n133: \n134: - **GIVEN** sandboxes in \"Unknown\" or \"Failed\" state for > 1 hour\n135: - **WHEN** the garbage collector runs\n136: - **THEN** the handler SHALL identify stale sandboxes\n137: - **AND** SHALL automatically clean up stale sandboxes\n138: - **AND** SHALL emit events for stale sandbox cleanup\n139: \n140: ---\n141: \n142: ## Scenario: Lifecycle Events\n143: \n144: ### AR-006-040: Emit Deletion Event\n145: \n146: - **GIVEN** a sandbox is deleted\n147: - **THEN** the handler SHALL emit a Kubernetes Event\n148: - **AND** SHALL include deletion reason, initiated by, and timestamp\n149: \n150: ### AR-006-041: Webhook Notification on Deletion\n151: \n152: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with deletion webhook configured\n153: - **THEN** the handler SHALL send POST notification to the webhook URL\n154: - **AND** SHALL include sandbox metadata in the request body\n155: - **AND** SHALL retry up to 3 times on failure\n156: - **AND** SHALL proceed with deletion regardless of webhook response\n157: \n158: ### AR-006-042: Deletion Audit Log\n159: \n160: - **GIVEN** a sandbox deletion operation\n161: - **THEN** the handler SHALL log:\n162:   - Sandbox identifier (SessionID, name)\n163:   - Namespace\n164:   - Deletion reason (explicit, TTL, idle, stale)\n165:   - Initiator (user, system)\n166:   - Duration from deletion request to completion\n167:   - Resources cleaned up\n168: \n169: ---\n170: \n171: ## Scenario: Resource Cleanup\n172: \n173: ### AR-006-050: Cleanup Associated Services\n174: \n175: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with associated Services\n176: - **WHEN** the sandbox is deleted\n177: - **THEN** the handler SHALL delete all Services owned by the sandbox\n178: - **AND** SHALL use ownerReference for automatic cleanup verification\n179: \n180: ### AR-006-051: Cleanup ConfigMaps and Secrets\n181: \n182: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with injected ConfigMaps or Secrets\n183: - **WHEN** the sandbox is deleted\n184: - **THEN** the handler SHALL delete ConfigMaps if marked for deletion\n185: - **AND** SHALL NOT delete Secrets (they may be shared)\n186: - **AND** SHALL log cleanup actions\n187: \n188: ### AR-006-052: Cleanup PVCs\n189: \n190: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with PVCs\n191: - **WHEN** the sandbox is deleted\n192: - **THEN** the handler SHALL handle PVC cleanup based on ReclaimPolicy\n193: - **AND** SHALL delete PVCs with ReclaimPolicy=Delete\n194: - **AND** SHALL retain PVCs with ReclaimPolicy=Retain\n195: \n196: ---\n197: \n198: ## Scenario: Error Handling\n199: \n200: ### AR-006-060: Deletion Failure Handling\n201: \n202: - **GIVEN** a sandbox deletion request\n203: - **WHEN** the Kubernetes API returns an error during deletion\n204: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return appropriate HTTP status code\n205: - **AND** SHALL include error message with cause details\n206: - **AND** SHALL log the error for debugging\n207: - **AND** SHALL retry deletion up to 3 times for transient errors\n208: \n209: ### AR-006-061: Orphaned Resource Cleanup\n210: \n211: - **GIVEN** a sandbox whose Pod was deleted externally\n212: - **WHEN** the garbage collector detects the orphan\n213: - **THEN** the handler SHALL clean up the sandbox record\n214: - **AND** SHALL clean up any orphaned Services or ConfigMaps\n215: - **AND** SHALL emit an event for orphan cleanup\n216: \n217: ### AR-006-062: Finalizer Handling\n218: \n219: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with finalizers\n220: - **WHEN** deletion is requested\n221: - **THEN** the handler SHALL execute all finalizers\n222: - **AND** SHALL remove finalizer only after successful execution\n223: - **AND** SHALL handle stuck finalizers with force deletion\n224: \n225: ---\n226: \n227: ## References\n228: \n229: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md`\n230: - Related AR: AR-005 (Sandbox 创建处理器)\n231: - Sandbox CRD: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n232: - Garbage Collector: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n233: - API group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n\n(End of file - total 233 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Sandbox deletion and lifecycle management features in `pkg/workloadmanager`. This includes cleanup of expired sandboxes, graceful termination, force deletion, and lifecycle hooks.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-006\n- **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n- **Depends On**: AR-005 (Sandbox 创建处理器)\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Sandbox Deletion\n\n### AR-006-001: Delete Sandbox by SessionID\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775843727761,"end":1775843727769}}}}
